</table>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="300">1.2. Searching for items</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Search for the item and access your entire product catalogue.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Searching for items:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p><a href="/en/app/installation#1100">Log into the plentymarkets app</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on the menu icon (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-bars  "></i></span>) in the top left corner of the app.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on <span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-search  "></i></span> <strong>Item search</strong>.<br>
→ The item search opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a search criteria, e.g. an item ID.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on <span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-search  "></i></span> <strong>Search</strong>.<br>
→ A list of items matching the search criteria is displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select an item (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-check  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The detailed view is shown.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Viewing stock information</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Tap on the boxes (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-cubes  "></i></span>) to see stock information. Then tap on the three dots (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-ellipsis-h  "></i></span>) if you want to <a href="/en/app/functions/warehouse-management/receiving-rebooking#500">replenish the stock</a> or if you want to <a href="/en/app/functions/item-search#400">print the item label</a>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="400">1.3. Printing labels with the plentymarkets app</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can use the app to manually generate labels for specific items.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Have you met all the requirements?</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Before you can print labels with the app, you have to:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>download a tool called plentyBase and <a href="/en/app/installation#2050">link it to the app</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>use templates to design your labels</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>specify which <a href="/en/app/functions/item-search#200">label template and printer</a> you want to use</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Printing labels with the plentymarkets app:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p><a href="/en/app/functions/item-search#300">Search for the item in the app</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on the boxes (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-cubes  "></i></span>) to see stock information.<br>
→ The storage locations of the item are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on the three dots (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-ellipsis-h  "></i></span>).<br>
→ Additional options are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on <span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-print  "></i></span> <strong>Print item label</strong>.<br>
→ The label is printed.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="500">2. Customer search</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The plentymarkets app makes it easy to search for customers while on the go.
Do you need to look up a customer’s email address or telephone number?
Do you want to check whether you have special payment conditions for this customer? For example, if this customer receives a percentage discount if he pays within a certain time frame?
The plentymarkets app makes it possible.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The plentymarkets app includes a customer search function, which is described on this page. First, <a href="/en/app/functions/item-search#600">configure a few basic settings</a> and decide what you want the search results to look like. These settings will go into effect when you <a href="/en/app/functions/item-search#700">search for customers</a> later.</p>
</div>
