<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1100">3.3. Filters</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>When you <a href="/en/app/functions/item-search#1000">search for orders</a>, the app automatically loads your newest orders.
But maybe you want to search for orders that are in a specific status or that came from a specific sales platform.
Simply use filters to narrow down the search results! You can also save your most frequently used search criteria so you don’t have to re-enter the filter parameters every time you search.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Filtering orders:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p><a href="/en/app/installation#1100">Log into the plentymarkets app</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on the menu icon (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-bars  "></i></span>) in the top left corner of the app.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on <span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-list-alt  "></i></span> <strong>Orders</strong>.<br>
→ Your orders will be loaded.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on the filter icon (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-filter  "></i></span>) in the top right corner.<br>
→ The filter settings are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the appropriate filters.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tap on <span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-filter  "></i></span> <strong>Apply</strong>.<br>
→ The orders that match the filter criteria will be displayed.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
